description: z(1) = 0, and for any n > 0, z(4*n-2) = z(n) + k(n), z(4*n-1) = z(n) + i*k(n), z(4*n) = z(n) - k(n) and z(4*n+1) = z(n) - i*k(n) where k(n) is the least positive integer not leading to a duplicate term in sequence z (and i denotes the imaginary unit); a(n) is the imaginary part of z(n).
